            "                    \"Any and all disputes relating to these Terms; Person shall email our legal department to inquire further,legal@madinagroup.co.tz\\n\");\n" +
            "            }else if(type.equalsIgnoreCase(\"privacy-policy\")){\n" +
            "                txtAboutus.setText(\"PRIVACY POLICY\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"GENERAL\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tFasalbook or https://www.Fasalbook.co.tz/ (\\\"our\\\", \\\"us\\\", \\\"we\\\", \\\"Website\\\", \\\"Fasalbook\\\", \\\"Fasalbook's mobile applications/websites\\\") is committed to the protection of Information provided by the users (\\\"you\\\", \\\"your\\\", \\\"users\\\") to us. You agree that your use of Fasalbook’s services or our interface implies your consent to the collection and use of your Information in accordance with the terms of this Privacy Policy (\\\"Privacy Policy\\\").\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tWe take the privacy of our users seriously. We are committed to safeguarding the privacy of our users while providing a personalized and valuable service. In addition to this Privacy Policy, we have taken the following steps to further safeguard your privacy:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"3.\\tFasalbook has established a set of \\\"Binding Corporate Rules\\\". These Binding Corporate Rules are a commitment by us to protect your Information regardless of where the data resides. Depending upon where you live, the Binding Corporate Rules may provide additional privacy rights through your local privacy regulator or government. For more information about our Binding Corporate Rules, including information on how to contact us with any questions, write to us at legal@Fasalbook.co.tz\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"INFORMATION COLLECTED\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tTraffic Data Collected\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"We automatically track and collect the following categories of information when you visit our Website:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\tIP addresses;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tDomain servers;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\tTypes of computers accessing the Website;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iv.\\tTypes of web browsers used to access the Website;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"v.\\tReferring source which may have sent you to the Website; and\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"vi.\\tOther information associated with the interaction of your browser and the Website (collectively \\\"Traffic Data\\\").\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tInformation Collected from You\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"In order for you to access certain areas of the Website, we may require you to provide us with certain information (\\\"Personal Information\\\"). Personal Information includes the following information:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\tYour full name, address, e-mail address, telephone number, date of birth and bank details and any proof of your identity and/or address that we may request;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tDetails of any transactions you carry out through our Application or Website using your Fasalbook Wallet account and of the fulfilment of your requests;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\tDetails of any bank account (including but not limited to, account holder, account name, account number, sort code, Transaction Authentication Number \\\"TAN\\\"), or any other documents as necessary by us;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iv.\\tYour participation in any promotion sponsored by us;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"v.\\tCorrespondence that you send us;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"vi.\\tCalls that we make to you or you make to us;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"vii.\\tSurveys that you complete through the Application/Website or based on our request;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"viii.\\tInformation collected through cookies. Please see Paragraph I (Cookies) of this Privacy Policy for more details;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ix.\\tYour IP address, log-in times, operating system and browser type; and\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"x.\\tDetails of your visits to our Application and Website including, but not limited to, Traffic Data, location data, weblogs and other communication data, whether this is required for our own billing purposes or otherwise and the resources that you access whilst using our Services.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"3.\\tIn order to fulfil our legal obligations to prevent fraud and money laundering, we will obtain information about you from third party agencies (\\\"Third Party Information\\\"), including your history, court judgements and bankruptcies, from credit bureau and fraud prevention agencies when you open a Fasalbookaccount and at any time when we feel it is necessary to prevent fraud and minimize our financial risks. Please refer to Anti-Money Laundering Policy Paragraph of this Privacy Policy for further details. Personal Information and Third-Party Information are collectively referred to as \\\"Information\\\".\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"USE AND STORAGE OF INFORMATION\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tWe use your Information for the following purposes:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\tTo operate and administer your wallet account and to provide services that you have requested;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tTo carry out your instructions to make and receive payments and undertake transactions using our services, including verifying that you have sufficient funds in your wallet to make such payments;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\tTo allow you to participate in interactive features of the Application and Website;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iv.\\tTo notify you about changes to our service(s);\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"v.\\tTo improve our internal customer training,\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"vi.\\tTo comply with financial services regulations including retention of financial information and transactions;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"vii.\\tFor financial and identity checks, fraud prevention checks, anti-money laundering and credit checks;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"viii.\\tFor customer service, including answering questions and responding to feedback and complaints;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ix.\\tTo enhance the security of our services;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"x.\\tTo ensure that content on our Application and Website is presented in the most effective manner for you and for your computer; and\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"xi.\\tTo provide you with information, products or services that you request from us or which we feel may interest you.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tRetention of Data.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"We are required under applicable laws to retain certain records for a period of at least ten (10) years after closure of your wallet account, which will include your personal data such as your name, contact details, customer number and transaction history, etc. (\\\"Retained Data\\\"). Other than the Retained Data, we will delete and destroy all Personal Information that we hold about you when you (or we) terminate your wallet account. We do not store your online wallet login PIN, TAN and/or password.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\tPlease note that we will not store your mobile money/bank information.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tPlease note that we will never ask you to disclose your personal or security details by e-mail. If you receive any e-mail purportedly from Fasalbook requesting your personal or security details, please do not respond to it any manner (\\\"Such E-mail\\\"). Please forward any Such E-mail to legal@Fasalbook.co.tz and thereafter delete the e-mail immediately.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"DISCLOSURE OF INFORMATION\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tWe do not disclose your Information to any third parties’ other than the Website's affiliates and the following:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\ta prospective buyer of our business or a buyer of a substantial number of the shares in our business;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tthe police, other lawful enforcement body, regulatory body or court if we are under a duty or required by law to disclose or share your personal data, or to protect the rights, property, or safety of ourselves or our group companies, our customers, or others;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\tFinancial institutions with whom we partner to jointly provide better services, facilities or products to you. These financial institutions may only use your information for providing to you their services and market Fasalbook related products without requiring your further consent.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iv.\\tthird parties where you have expressed an interest in receiving information about their goods and services;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"v.\\tthird parties who referred you to us initially and to whom we owe a commission payment as a result of the referral. Where the commission payment is based on transaction volumes, numbers or types of transactions, we may share that information with that third party, but we will not disclose the full details of each of your transactions without your further written consent; and\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"vi.\\tthird parties we may occasionally use to provide you with the services that you have requested. We require these third parties to not use your personal information for any other purpose.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tWe also use Information in aggregate form (so that no individual user is identified):\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\tTo build up marketing profiles;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tTo aid strategic development;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\tTo audit usage of the Website\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"3.\\tWe reserve the right to disclose Information if required to do so by law or if we believe that it is necessary to do so to protect and defend the rights, property or personal safety of the Website, or its users.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"FRAUD AND CREDIT AGENCIES\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tWhen you open a Fasalbook account, at intervals of up to every 3 (three) months and at any other time we feel it is necessary to do so to protect our financial interests and prevent money-laundering or fraud, we share certain information about you and your account, financial history and transactions as part of our normal business operations with banks, payment facilitator partners, paymentgateway and processing services, identity verification service providers and credit reference agencies (including, but not limited to) to identify and verify users, to limit our exposure to fraud and other criminal activities and to manage our financial risk. We can provide you with a list of the credit reference agencies we use upon your written request to Fasalbook’s Legal Department. When conducting identification or fraud prevention checks, the relevant parties may retain a record of our query along with your information and may share this information with other fraud prevention agencies. If you want to know what information these companies hold about you, you can write to them to request access to your information.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tAnti-Money Laundering Policy\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"In order to comply with anti-money laundering laws that exist in various jurisdictions we reserve the right to report suspicious transactions or any other information to federal or local authorities and law enforcement agencies within those jurisdictions. In exchange for us permitting you to participate in, use and access our Application/Website and services you hereby grant us the right to report any transactions or information which we deem suspicious or strange, as determined solely by Fasalbook acting in its sole discretion. Examples of a suspicious transaction include but are not limited to use of funds suspected to be derived from illegal activities, any suspected intention to conceal or disguise funds derived from illegal activities, or suspicion that the involvement of our Application/Website and services is in any manner intended to facilitate criminal activity. If for any reason we are of the belief or become aware of any transaction which we deem suspicious in nature, we may without prior notice or explanation to you take the following actions, which are in addition to all other rights and remedies available to us under this Privacy Policy, at law or in equity:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\treport such transaction to the applicable local authorities and law enforcement agencies;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tde-activate or terminate your wallet account forthwith;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\twithhold any funds held in your walletaccount; and/or\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iv.\\trestrict you from registering a wallet account on or with our Application and Website or any of our affiliated websites.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"COMMUNICATIONS\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tWe may contact you via the e-mail address and phone number registered with your Fasalbook wallet account. You may also receive system-generated transactional e-mails such as confirmations, notification of receipt of payments, notification of password changes etc. which are necessary for the appropriate operation and administration of your wallet account. You expressly consent to receive such communications from us, irrespective of whether your phone number is registered on the National Do Not Call Registry.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tAs a Fasalbook wallet account holder, you will occasionally receive information by e-mail from us, unless you have expressly chosen not to receive such communication, about products, services and special deals which we think will be of interest to you via our newsletter. You can change whether or not you receive newsletters from us. However, kindly note that you will still receive communication regarding your wallet account such as transactional e-mails or other notifications affecting the operation of your Fasalbook wallet account or our legal relationship.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"PHISHING\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tPhishing is the name given to attempts to steal personal details and financial account details from an application and/or website user. \\\"Phishers\\\" use fake or \\\"spoof\\\" emails to lead users to counterfeit websites where the user is tricked into entering their personal details, such as bank account/mobile money, user names and passwords.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tIf you receive such an e-mail or are asked for your password by anyone claiming to work for us please forward the e-mail or report the incident by e-mail to our Data Protection Officer at legal@Fasalbook.co.tz.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"LINKS TO OUR WEBSITE AND OTHER WEBSITES\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tOur Website may, from time to time, contain links to and from the websites of our partner networks, advertisers and affiliates. If you follow a link to any of these websites, please note that these websites have their own terms of use and privacy policies and that we do not accept any responsibility or liability for these policies. Please check these policies before you submit any personal data to these websites. Please also note that the products and services offered on these websites may be limited to persons located or residing in only that particular jurisdiction. In addition, the content on these linked websites may not be intended for persons located or residing in jurisdictions that restrict the distribution of such content.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tOur Website also includes social media features, such as the Facebook Like button and widgets, such as the \\\"Share this\\\" button or interactive mini-programs that run on our site. These features may collect your IP address, which page you are visiting on our Application and/or Website, and may set a Cookie to enable the feature to function properly. Social media features and widgets are either hosted by a third party or hosted directly on our Website. Your interactions with these features are governed by the privacy policy of the company providing it.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"3.\\tYou must always obtain the prior written approval of Fasalbook before creating a hyperlink in any form from a third-party website to any webpage on the Fasalbook Website. Fasalbook may or may not give such approval at its absolute discretion. In normal circumstances, we may only approve a hyperlink which displays plainly our name or website address. Any use or display of our logos, trade names and trademarks as a hyperlink will not be approved unless in very exceptional circumstances and may be subject to a fee as Fasalbook may determine at its absolute discretion. Fasalbook is not responsible for the setup of any hyperlink from a third-party website to any Fasalbook website. Any links so set up shall not constitute any form of co-operation with, or endorsement by, Fasalbook of such third-party website. Any link to our application or website shall always be an active and direct link to our website and shall be made directly to the home or front page of our website only and no \\\"framing\\\" or \\\"deep-linking\\\" of any webpage of our Website or content is allowed. Please contact Fasalbook’s Legal Department if you wish to create a hyperlink to any page of our Website on a third-party website.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"COOKIES\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\t\\\"Cookies\\\" are small computer files that are transferred to your computer's hard drive that contain information such as user ID, user preferences, lists of pages visited and activities conducted while browsing the Application and or Website. At your option, expense and responsibility, you may block cookies or delete cookies from your hard drive. However, by disabling cookies, you may not have access to the entire set of features of the Application and/or Website.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tGenerally, we use Cookies to customize your experience on our Website and to store your password so you do not have to re-enter it each time you visit the Website.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"3.\\tIn addition, our business partners may use Cookies to provide us with anonymous data and information regarding the use of our Application/Website. Specifically, some of our business partners use Cookies to show the App/Website's ads on other websites on the internet as a result of you using the Application/Website. Such Cookies do not contain any Information. You may opt out of receiving Cookies placed by such third-party vendors by visiting the opt-out page.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"4.\\tOther Cookies used by our business partners may collect other non-personally identifying information, such as the computer's IP address, type of operating system, type of internet browsing software, what web pages were viewed at what time, the geographic location of your internet service provider and demographic information, such as gender and age range. This information is used to provide the Application or Website with more information about our user's demographics and internet behaviors. You may find out more about the information collected and how to opt-out of receiving these Cookies by visiting our partner's website.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"5.\\tWe do not link the information stored in these Cookies directly to any of your information you submit while on the Application and or Website.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"6.\\tIn order to comply with legislation, we have reviewed the use of Cookies on our Application or Website and set out the information below. This is to ensure that you are aware of these cookies and are able to give your consent for the placing of some or all of these cookies on your device when you use our Application and Website. In summary, we use the following types of cookies:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Strictly Necessary Cookies\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"These are cookies which are essential for our Website to operate such as those which identify you so you can log into your Fasalbook account. They allow you to move around our Application and Website and use the services you have requested. These Cookies will be activated when you enter our systems and as you use our Services.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Compliance Cookies\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"These include Cookies which are necessary to assist in meeting our regulatory compliance obligations, such as anti-money laundering and anti-fraud obligations, and prevent your Fasalbook wallet account from being hijacked. These cookies will be activated when you enter our systems and as you use our Services.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Performance Cookies\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"These are Cookies that help us to improve how our systems works and to deliver a better service to you. For example, they will assess which pages you visit most often or if you get an error message. They also allow us to see if you have used the Services of one of our group or affiliated companies. All information collected by these Cookies is aggregated and therefore anonymous.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Functionality Cookies\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"These Cookies allow us to deliver a more personalized service to you and allow our Application and Website to remember choices you have made such as the language you prefer or the region you are in. They may also be used to provide services you have requested such as being able to comment on one of our blogs.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Third Party Cookies\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"When you visit a page on our Application or Website with content embedded from third parties, for example, YouTube or Twitter, Cookies may be downloaded onto your device. We do not set or control these Cookies. If you are concerned about the types of Cookies that may be downloaded you check the third-party websites for more information about these Cookies.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"We may use other Cookies from time to time in accordance with this Privacy Policy. By using our Website and other online services, you acknowledge that we may use some or all of the Cookies set out in this Privacy Policy and you agree that we can place performance and functionality Cookies on your device when you use our Website. If you do not agree to this you should cease using our systems and online services or adjust your browser settings.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Blocking Cookies\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Should you want to continue using our services but restrict our use of Cookies, you can block Cookies by activating the setting on your browser which allows you to refuse the setting of all or some cookies. However, if you use your browser settings to block all Cookies (including Strictly Necessary and/or Compliance Cookies, as described above) you may not be able to access all or parts of our Services. Our systems may issue some of the Cookies described above as soon as you visit our Application/Website unless you have adjusted your setting so that it will refuse Cookies.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"WEB BEACONS\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"In limited circumstances, we also may use \\\"Web Beacons\\\" to collect anonymous, non-Information about your use of our Application/Website and the websites of selected sponsors and advertisers, and your use of e-mails, special promotions or newsletters we send to you. Web Beacons are tiny graphic image files imbedded in a web page or email that provide a presence on the web page or e-mail and send back to its home server information from the user's browser or application. The information collected by web beacons allows us to statistically monitor how many people are using the Website and selected sponsors' and advertisers' websites, or opening our e-mails, and for what purposes.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"WEB ANALYTICS\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"We may use third party website analytics services in connection with the Application or Website. These website analytics services do not collect information that you do not voluntarily enter into the Website. These services do not track your browsing habits across websites which do not use their services. We are using the information collected from these services to find usability problems to make the Website easier to use. The recordings will never identify you or your account.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"SECURITY CHECKS, REVIEW AND RELEASES\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"To maintain a high level of security, we reserve the right to conduct a security review at any time to validate your identity, verify your financial transactions and further document your consent to this Agreement. To facilitate these security checks, you agree to provide such identification or other information or documentation as we, in our sole and unfettered discretion, deem necessary. If you fail to comply with any security request, we reserve the right to void your Fasalbook wallet account. You will be notified of such verification request by e-mail or telephone and your wallet account balances will be forfeited if you fail to provide us with such requested documentation and information within the time period reasonably specified by us. Such request for documentation and information may include a sworn affidavit of identity and eligibility, release of liability in favour of us and publicity authorization.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"USER CHOICE\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"You may choose not to provide us with any Information while accessing the Application or Website. In such an event, you can still access much of the system; However, you will not be able to access and use those portions of the Services that require your Information.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"CONFIDENTIALITY AND SECURITY\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Except as otherwise provided in this Privacy Policy, we will keep your Information private and will not share it with third-parties, unless we believe in good faith that disclosure of your Information or any other information we collect about you is necessary to:\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"i.\\tcomply with a court order or other legal process;\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"ii.\\tProtect the rights, property or safety of our company or another party.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iii.\\tEnforce our Terms of Use or\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"iv.\\tRespond to claims that any posting or other content violates the rights of third parties\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"You hereby give consent to Fasalbook to share your KYC documents toRegulatory Bodies, Government agencies on our behalf.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"PUBLIC INFORMATION\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"Any information that you may reveal in a review posting or other online discussion or forum is intentionally open to the public and is not in any way private. You should think carefully before disclosing any personally identifiable information in any public forum. What you have written may be seen and/or collected by third parties and may be used by others in ways we are unable to control or predict.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"SECURITY\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tWe are committed to ensuring that your Information is secure. To prevent unauthorized access or disclosure of Information we have physical, electronic and managerial procedures in place to keep your information safe. Once logged into your wallet account, all internet communication is secured using Transport Layer Security (TLS) technology and the connection is encrypted and authenticated using AES 128bit encryption key and uses Elliptic Curve Diffie-hellman key exchange (ECDHE) RSA as a key exchange mechanism.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"However, this high level of protection can only be effective if you follow certain security practices yourself. You must never share your wallet account or login details with anyone. If you are concerned that any of your login details have been compromised, you can change them any time once you are logged on but you should always also immediately contact customer services at Fasalbook “Contact us” and tell us why you think your login details have been compromised. Please read our Terms and Conditions for further information on how to keep your Fasalbook wallet account safe.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tAlthough we make good faith efforts to store Information in a secure operating environment that is not open to the public, you should understand that there is no such thing as complete security, and we do not guarantee that there will be no unintended disclosures of your Information. If we become aware that your Information has been disclosed in a manner not in accordance with this Privacy Policy, we will use reasonable efforts to notify you of the nature and extent of the disclosure (to the extent we know that information) as soon as reasonably possible and as permitted by law.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"POLICY AMMENDMENTS\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"We reserve the right, at any time, to add to, change, update, or modify this Privacy Policy so please review it frequently. If we do, then we will notify you here, as well as by posting a notice on our Website and, where appropriate, a link to the modified policy so that you can review it. In all cases, use of information we collect is subject to the Privacy Policy in effect at the time such information is collected.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"YOUR RIGHTS\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"You have a legal right to a copy of any Information about you held by us. You also have a right to correct any errors in that Information. As mentioned above, you have a right to request that we cease to use your Information for direct marketing purposes.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"RESTRICTION OF LIABILITY\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tWe make no claims, promises or guarantees about the accuracy, completeness, or adequacy of the contents on this Policy and Application/Website and expressly disclaim liability for errors and omissions in the contents of our Application and Website.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"2.\\tNo warranty of any kind, implied, expressed or statutory, including but not limited to the warranties of non-infringement of third party rights, title, merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose and freedom from computer virus, is given with respect to the contents of the Application/Website or its hyperlinks to other internet resources.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"3.\\tReference in this Application/Website to any specific commercial products, processes, or services, or the use of any trade, firm or corporation name is for the information and convenience of the public, and does not constitute endorsement, recommendation, or favoring by us.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"4.\\tThe contents (partly or wholly) of ourapplication and website maybe under copyright and/or trademark of their original author(s) unless otherwise noted on the page itself.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"5.\\tIf you have questions or concerns, feel free to e-mail us or to correspond atContact us and we will attempt to address your issue.\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\""


    val PrivacyPolicy = "\"About Us\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"GENERAL\\n\" +\n" +
            "                        \"1.\\tFasalbook or https://www.Fasalbook.co.tz/ (\\\"our\\\", \\\"us\\\", \\\"we\\\", \\\"Website\\\", \\\"Fasalbook\\\", \\\"Fasalbook's mobile applications/websites\\\") is committed to the protection of Information provided by the users (\\\"you\\\", \\\"your\\\", \\\"users\\\") to us. You agree that your use of Fasalbook’s services or our interface implies your consent to the collection and use of your Information in accordance with the terms of this Privacy Policy (\\\"Privacy Policy\\\").\\n\" +\n" +
